# Trying Code Coloring
1. Create Fenced Code Block First
>>>Standard Markdown is done by surrounding text with with 4 spaces at beginning of each line
>>>Fenced Code in GFM is ``` code ```
>>>>>>Although fenced code blocks don't have to be preceded by a blank line like indented code blocks do, it's recommended
>>>>>>Remember within lists, you have to indent non-fenced code blocks eight spaces to render them properly

## Example


        public class HelloWorld
       {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		System.out.println("Hello World!");
	}
        }


